'''Farah Weheliye Addo''' ({{lang-so|Faarax Wehliye Caddoow}}, {{lang-ar|فرح ادو}}), also known as '''Sindiko''' (born 1935<ref name="FIFA">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/aboutfifa/organisation/president/news/newsid=954502/|title=Farah Addo dies|date=20 November 2008|work=FIFA.com}}</ref> or 1940,<ref name="BBC">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/africa/7741495.stm|title=Somali official Addo dies|date=21 November 2008|publisher=BBC SPORT}}</ref> died November 19, 2008<ref name="FIFA"/>), was a prominent [[Somali people|Somali]] [[sports]] [[Administration (business)|administrator]].
==Biography== Addo hailed from the [[Harti (Abgaal)|Harti]] [[Abgaal]] clan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mareeg.com/fidsan.php?sid=6443&tirsan=3|title=Somalia: Farah Addo elected chairman of football federation|author=|date=|publisher=Mareeg}}</ref> He spent many years in a leadership role in international sports. A former referee, he would later become chairman of the [[Somali Football Federation|Somalian Football Association]], the [[Council for East and Central Africa Football Associations]], and of the [[Somalian Olympic Committee]]. Farah was also a former first vice-president of the [[Confederation of African Football|African Football Confederation]] (CAF) and an Honorary Member of the organisation.<ref name="FIFA"/>
Addo died on Wednesday November 19, 2008 in [[Egypt]], at the age of 73.<ref name="FIFA"/>
