'''Nancy Charest''' (November 28, 1959 – March 1, 2014) was a [[Canadians|Canadian]] politician. She represented the electoral district of [[Matane (provincial electoral district)|Matane]] in the [[National Assembly of Quebec]] from 2003 to 2007 as a member of the [[Quebec Liberal Party]]. She was defeated by [[Pascal Bérubé]] of the [[Parti Québécois]] in the [[Quebec general election, 2007|2007 provincial election]].

She ran as the [[Liberal Party of Canada]]'s candidate for the district of [[Haute-Gaspésie—La Mitis—Matane—Matapédia]] in the [[Canadian federal election, 2008|2008 federal election]]. She lost to [[Bloc Québécois]] incumbent [[Jean-Yves Roy]], but received the highest vote percentage of any non-winning Liberal candidate in the province outside of the [[Montreal]] area. {{citation needed|date=September 2014}}

Charest was found dead on March 1, 2014 along a road in her native Matane, Quebec. The cause of death was [[hypothermia]], caused by exposure while Charest was heavily [[Alcohol intoxication|intoxicated]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cjad.com/cjad-news/2014/09/24/coroner-death-of-mna-caused-by-hypothermia|title=Coroner: Death of MNA caused by hypothermia|publisher=CJAD Newse|date=September 24, 2014|accessdate=2014-12-01}}</ref> She was 54 years old.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.montrealgazette.com/news/Former+Liberal+Nancy+Charest+found+dead/9569323/story.html|title=Former Liberal MNA Nancy Charest found dead|publisher=Montreal Gazette|date=March 2, 2014|accessdate=2014-03-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Bernard|last=Dupéré|title=Décès de l'ancienne députée Nancy Charest|work=TVA Nouvelles|date=March 2, 2014|url=http://tvanouvelles.ca/lcn/infos/regional/estduquebec/archives/2014/03/20140302-130012.html|accessdate=March 2, 2014|trans-title=Death of the former member Nancy Charest}}</ref>

